content.text:
This claim is a **counterfactual** statement. It says "If the football player... **had been born** one week later... he **would have** represented a different national team."

This describes a hypothetical "what if" scenario — what would have happened if a player's birthday were different. The database only records what actually happened, not what would have occurred under hypothetical changes to a player's birth date. There is no way to verify from the data whether being born one week later would cause someone to represent a different national team.

Per the workflow rules, counterfactual claims must always be classified as NOT ENOUGH INFO.
